keColor=#b85450;fontSize=10;" edge="1" parent="1" source="4571_4" target="4571_23"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="4571_25" value="APPROACHES per stage —  Base functionality: dry-run / --quick smoke, no API (A6 · A8).   Meets spec: schema validation + Run-Contract conformance (R3 · G1 · G2).   Challenge: Option A meta-eval + Option B independence controls + Option C ensemble.   Independence (A2 · D1): attacker ≠ judge ≠ target model families · neutral re-judge · multi-seed + mutator ablation (avoids co-adaptation confound).   Every gate deterministic (A1 · R9); nothing bypasses the adapter (R2). This pipeline is workflow W-C." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#cccccc;dashed=1;fontSize=10;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontColor=#555555;spacingLeft=8;spacingTop=6;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="500" width="1560" height="130" as="geometry"/></mxCell></root></mxGraphModel></diagram><diagram name="Frontier Vendor Integration Map" id="Frontier_Vendor_Integration_Map"><mxGraphModel dx="1420" dy="900" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1600" pageHeight="1160" math="0" shadow="0"><root><mxCell id="0"/><mxCell id="1" parent="0"/><mxCell id="4979_1" value="Frontier Vendor Integration Map — where each plugs in (lane · layer · harnesses)" style="text;html=1;fontSize=20;fontStyle=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="18" width="1200" height="30" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="4979_2" value="Modes: DRIVER (behind Run Contract) · DETECTOR (floors judge) · GUARDRAIL (inline + test target) · PLATFORM (orchestrate-above) · SUBSTRATE (glue)" style="text;html=1;fontSize=12;align=left;fontColor=#555555;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="48" width="1300" height="20" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="4979_3" value="ANTHROPIC — Petri / Bloom (DRIVER · autonomous alignment &amp; behavioral auditing) · Claude Agent SDK + MCP (SUBSTRATE)   →   Data plane · H1.3, agentic, H2.4   ·   aligned ✓" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="110" width="1520" height="70" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="4979_4" value="NVIDIA — Garak (DRIVER · vuln scanner, 50+ probes, Agent-breaker/GOAT) · NeMo Guardrails (GUARDRAIL + resilience test-target) · Aegis (safety model)   →   Data plane / inline · H1.2, H2.1, H2.3, H4.1   ·   aligned ✓" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#d5e8d4;strokeColor=#82b366;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="190" width="1520" height="70" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="4979_5" value="MICROSOFT — PyRIT (DRIVER · orchestration: Crescendo, encoding, agentic ASR) · Azure Foundry RT Agent (CLOUD BACKEND) · Content Safety / Prompt Shields (GUARDRAIL) · Presidio (DETECTOR · PII/CPNI floor)   →   Data plane / inline · H2.1, H1.2, H2.2, H2.3   ·   aligned ✓" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="270" width="1520" height="80" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="4979_6" value="CISCO — AI Defense (PLATFORM)  →  ORCHESTRATE-ABOVE (decided): consumed BEHIND the Run Contract as driver + OWASP·NIST·MITRE control-map (H5.3) + continuous validation.  Our deterministic gate stays authoritative.  ✓" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#9673a6;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="360" width="1520" height="80" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="4979_7" value="OURS (glue) — LiteLLM (adapter · single I/O path · ≠ AT&amp;T Model Router) · Inspect AI (scoring substrate) · Glasswing MAP-Elites (DRIVER · QD coverage) · H1.5 Bias &amp; Fairness (Phase-1) · deterministic Gate + Judge Quorum + Detectors" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#999999;fontSize=12;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="450" width="1520" height="80" as="geometry"/></mxCell><mxCell id="4979_8" value="Integration rules —  All DRIVERS (incl. Cisco, orchestrate-above) plug behind the Run Contract (R3) and are compared by the W-C bake-off (Page 2).  GUARDRAILS are inline (§6.17) AND tested by the Resilience harness (H4.1) — a guardrail pass is not a harness verdict.  The AT&amp;T Model Router is AT&amp;T-owned; our adapter is a separate harness-I/O path.  Provider- &amp; model-independence (R2 · A2 · D1) preserved: nothing bypasses the adapter; attacker ≠ judge ≠ target families." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#cccccc;dashed=1;fontSize=10;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontColor=#555555;spacingLeft=8;spacingTop=6;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="548" width="1520" height="120" as="geometry"/></mxCell></root></mxGraphModel></diagram></mxfile>